This paper deals with the correctness of concurrent objects in the context of modern multicore architectures, which is a topic that falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. It also involves programming language theory and semantics, which is covered by the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper discusses the correctness notion of linearizability, which is a topic in Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The weak memory models discussed in the paper are relevant to Operating Systems (cs.OS). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the TSO, Power, and ARM architectures, which fall under the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
